First National Bank inMount Clemens, Mich., said it is seeking final regulatoryapproval to form First National Bank Corp, a bank holdingcompany, following shareholder approval Tuesday.    It said formation of First National Bank Corp will resultin a one-for-one stock exchange for shareholders of FirstNational Bank in Mount Clemens.    First National Bank Corp is the parent company of FirstNational Bank in Mount Clemens and Bankers Life Insurance Co, anewly created insurance subsidiary.    At the shareholders' meeting, the bank also reported 1986First National Bank earnings of 2,008,000 dlrs, or 2.22 dlrs ashare, up 11 pct from 1985's earnings of 1,811,000 dlrs, or2.00 dlrs a share.    Bank assets climbed to 276 mln dlrs from 240 mln dlrs in1985, it said. Reuter&#3;